import numpy as np

def to_one_hot(y,num_classes=10):
    results=np.zeros((len(y),num_classes))
    for i,label in enumerate(y):
        results[i,label]=1.
    return results

y_train_vec=to_one_hot(y_train)
y_test_vec=to_one_hot(y_test)

print('Shape of y_train_vec:'+str(y_train_vec.shape))
print('Shape of y_test_vec:'+str(y_test_vec.shape))

print(y_train[0])
print(y_train_vec[0])

# original encoder
from keras.layers import Dense,Input
from keras import models

input_img=Input(shape=(784,),name='input_img')

encode1=Dense(128,activation='relu',name='encode1')(input_img)
encode2=Dense(32,activation='relu',name='encode2')(encode1)
encode3=Dense(8,activation='relu',name='encode3')(encode2)

bottleneck=Dense(2,activation='relu',name='bottleneck')(encode3)
decode1=Dense(8,activation='relu',name='decode1')(bottleneck)
decode2=Dense(32,activation='relu',name='decode2')(decode1)
decode3=Dense(128,activation='relu',name='decode3')(decode2)
decode4=Dense(784,activation='relu',name='decode4')(decode3)

ae=models.Model(input_img,decode4)

ae.summary()

# try to use VAE
import keras
from keras.layers import Conv2D,Conv2DTranspose,Flatten,Dense,Reshape,Lambda,BatchNormalization,Activation,Dropout,MaxPooling2D
from keras import Input
from keras import layers
from keras import backend as K
from keras.models import Model
import numpy as np
import keras.losses as ls
from keras import regularizers

img_shape=(28,28,1)
batch_size=16
latent_dim=2

input_img=Input(shape=img_shape,name='encoder_input')

x=Conv2D(32,3,padding='same',activation='relu',name='encoder_0')(input_img)
x=Conv2D(64,3,padding='same',activation='relu',strides=(2,2),name='encoder_1')(x)
x=Conv2D(64,3,padding='same',activation='relu',name='encoder_2')(x)
x=Conv2D(64,3,padding='same',activation='relu',name='encoder_3')(x)
shape_before_flattening=K.int_shape(x)

x=Flatten(name='encoder_4')(x)
x=Dense(32,activation='relu',name='encoder_5')(x)

z_mean=Dense(latent_dim,name='output_mean')(x)
z_log_var=Dense(latent_dim,name='output_std')(x)

def sampling(args):
  z_mean,z_log_var=args
  epsilon=K.random_normal(shape=(K.shape(z_mean)[0],latent_dim),mean=0.,stddev=1.)
  return z_mean+K.exp(0.5*z_log_var)*epsilon

def vae_loss(x,z_decoded):
  x=K.flatten(x)
  z_decoded=K.flatten(z_decoded)
  xent_loss=keras.metrics.binary_crossentropy(x,z_decoded)
  kl_loss=(-5e-4)*K.mean(1+z_log_var-K.square(z_mean)-K.exp(z_log_var),axis=-1)
  return K.mean(xent_loss+kl_loss)

z=Lambda(sampling)([z_mean,z_log_var])



decoder_input=Input(K.int_shape(z)[1:],name='decoder_Input')
decode1=Dense(np.prod(shape_before_flattening[1:]),activation='relu',name='decoder_1')(decoder_input)
decode2=Reshape(shape_before_flattening[1:],name='decoder2')(decode1)
decode3=Conv2DTranspose(32,3,padding='same',activation='relu',strides=(2,2),name='decoder3')(decode2)
decode4=Conv2D(1,3,padding='same',activation='sigmoid',name='decoder4')(decode3)
decoder=Model(decoder_input,decode4)
z_decoded=decoder(z)

vae=Model(input_img,z_decoded)
vae.compile(optimizer='rmsprop',loss=vae_loss)
vae.summary()

# combine VAE with VGG16
import keras
from keras.layers import Conv2D,Conv2DTranspose,Flatten,Dense,Reshape,Lambda,BatchNormalization,Activation,Dropout,MaxPooling2D
from keras import Input
from keras import layers
from keras import backend as K
from keras.models import Model
import numpy as np

img_shape=(28,28,1)
batch_size=16
latent_dim=2

input_img=Input(shape=img_shape,name='encoder_input')

x=Conv2D(32,3,padding='same',activation='relu',name='encoder_0')(input_img)
x=Conv2D(64,3,padding='same',activation='relu',strides=(2,2),name='encoder_1')(x)
x=Conv2D(64,3,padding='same',activation='relu',name='encoder_2')(x)
x=Conv2D(64,3,padding='same',activation='relu',name='encoder_3')(x)
shape_before_flattening=K.int_shape(x)

x=Flatten(name='encoder_4')(x)
x=Dense(32,activation='relu',name='encoder_5')(x)

z_mean=Dense(latent_dim,name='output_mean')(x)
z_log_var=Dense(latent_dim,name='output_std')(x)
In [0]:
def sampling(args):
  z_mean,z_log_var=args
  epsilon=K.random_normal(shape=(K.shape(z_mean)[0],latent_dim),mean=0.,stddev=1.)
  return z_mean+K.exp(0.5*z_log_var)*epsilon
z=Lambda(sampling)([z_mean,z_log_var])
In [0]:
def vae_loss(x,z_decoded):
  x=K.flatten(x)
  z_decoded=K.flatten(z_decoded)
  xent_loss=keras.metrics.binary_crossentropy(x,z_decoded)
  kl_loss=(-5e-4)*K.mean(1+z_log_var-K.square(z_mean)-K.exp(z_log_var),axis=-1)
  return K.mean(xent_loss+kl_loss)

cl_input=Input(K.int_shape(z)[1:],name='classifier_input')
cl_1=Dense(np.prod(shape_before_flattening[1:]),activation='relu',name='classifier_1')(cl_input)
cl_2=Reshape(shape_before_flattening[1:],name='classifier_2')(cl_1)
cl_3=Conv2DTranspose(32,3,padding='same',activation='relu',strides=(2,2),name='classifier_3')(cl_2)
cl_4=Conv2D(1,3,padding='same',activation='sigmoid',name='classifier_4')(cl_3)

cl_5=Conv2D(64,3,activation=None,strides=1,kernel_initializer='he_normal',padding='same',name='classifier_5')(cl_4)
cl_6=BatchNormalization(name='classifier_6')(cl_5)
cl_7=Activation('relu',name='classifier_7')(cl_6)
cl_8=Conv2D(64,3,strides=1,padding='same',activation=None,kernel_initializer='he_normal',name='classifier_8')(cl_7)
cl_9=BatchNormalization(name='classifier_9')(cl_8)
cl_10=Activation('relu',name='classifier_10')(cl_9)
cl_11=MaxPooling2D(pool_size=2,strides=2,padding='valid',name='classifier_11')(cl_10)

cl_12=Conv2D(128,3,strides=1,padding='same',activation=None,kernel_initializer='he_normal',name='classifier_12')(cl_11)
cl_13=BatchNormalization(name='classifier_13')(cl_12)
cl_14=Activation('relu',name='classifier_14')(cl_13)
cl_15=Conv2D(128,(3,3),strides=1,padding='same',activation=None,kernel_initializer='he_normal',name='classifier_15')(cl_14)
cl_16=BatchNormalization(name='classifier_16')(cl_15)
cl_17=Activation('relu',name='classifier_17')(cl_16)
cl_18=MaxPooling2D(pool_size=2,strides=2,padding='valid',name='classifier_18')(cl_17)

cl_19=Conv2D(256,3,strides=1,padding='same',activation=None,kernel_initializer='he_normal',name='classifier_19')(cl_18)
cl_20=BatchNormalization(name='classifier_20')(cl_19)
cl_21=Activation('relu',name='classifier_21')(cl_20)
cl_22=Conv2D(256,3,strides=1,padding='same',activation=None,kernel_initializer='he_normal',name='classifier_22')(cl_21)
cl_23=BatchNormalization(name='classifier_23')(cl_22)
cl_24=Activation('relu',name='classifier_24')(cl_23)
cl_25=MaxPooling2D(pool_size=2,strides=2,padding='valid',name='classifier_25')(cl_24)

cl_26=Flatten(name='classifier_26')(cl_25)
cl_27=Dropout(0.5,name='classifier_27')(cl_26)
cl_28=Dense(128,activation='relu',kernel_initializer='he_normal',kernel_regularizer=regularizers.l2(0.01),name='classifier_28')(cl_27)
cl_output=Dense(10,activation='softmax',kernel_initializer='he_normal',name='classifier_output')(cl_28)

classifier=Model(cl_input,cl_output,name='classifier_VGG16')
z_classifier=classifier(z)

vae=Model(input_img,[z_decoded,z_classifier])

vae.summary()

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
from scipy.stats import norm

n=15
digit_size=28

figure=np.zeros((digit_size*n,digit_size*n))
grid_x=norm.ppf(np.linspace(0.05,0.95,n))
grid_y=norm.ppf(np.linspace(0.05,0.95,n))

for i,yi in enumerate(grid_x):
  for j,xi in enumerate(grid_y):
    z_sample=np.array([[xi,yi]])
    z_sample=np.tile(z_sample,batch_size).reshape(batch_size,2)
    x_decoded=decoder.predict(z_sample,batch_size=batch_size)
    digit=x_decoded[0].reshape(digit_size,digit_size)
    figure[i*digit_size:(i+1)*digit_size,j*digit_size:(j+1)*digit_size]=digit
plt.figure(figsize=(10,10))
plt.imshow(figure,cmap='Greys_r')
plt.show()

plt.legend()
plt.show()
